                    <li>1941 - Worked at a photo-chemical laboratory where he researched sound recording technology.</li>
                    <li>1945 - Founded Tokyo-Tsushin Kenkyusho (Tokyo Telecommunications Laboratory) Co.</li>
                    <li>1946 - Founded Tokyo-Tsushin-Kogyo Co. (Tokyo Telecommunications Engineering Corporation) with Akio Morita.</li>
                    <li>1949 - Developed magnetic recording tapes</li>
                    <li>1958 - Company name officially changed to Sony Corporation</li>
